    $('#node-eifer1').css('background-color', '#fff');
     // get the position
    $('#node-eifer1').mousedown(function() {
        $("#node-eifer1").mousemove(function() {
            console.log("moving...");
        });
        console.log("passing...");
    });
});
```

The problem is that I want to activate an event when the user is moving the ball. But, once you have moved the ball (it is a draggable element), and pass the mouse over the ball when the ball is moved, the event will be triggered again.

The desirable steps are:
- Move the ball to a wherever position and trigger the ``moving...`` text
- Once the mouse has been released (ie, the ball is placed where I want) the ``moving...`` text must not be triggered again unless I clicked the ball. [Note that what's going on, is that, this step is failing]. Refer to the console and you will see that ``moving`` text is printed when the ball is placed once it has been moved.

