jQuery and Sizzle follow the byte-wasting practice of using "true" instead of "1" in constant arguments to for in loops, such as following:
```javascript
// Add button/input type pseudos
for ( i in { radio: true, checkbox: true, file: true, password: true, image: true } ) {
	Expr.pseudos[ i ] = createInputPseudo( i );
}
for ( i in { submit: true, reset: true } ) {
	Expr.pseudos[ i ] = createButtonPseudo( i );
}
```

This could be rewritten as:
```javascript
// Add button/input type pseudos
for (i in {radio: 1, checkbox: 1, file: 1, password: 1, image: 1}) {
	Expr.pseudos[i] = createInputPseudo(i);
}
for (i in {submit: 1, reset: 1}) {
	Expr.pseudos[i] = createButtonPseudo(i);
}
```

