Based on this answer https://github.com/tmpvar/jsdom/issues/717#issuecomment-31620260 , the issue seems to be on jquery's side : `document.implementation.createHTMLDocument( "" )` creates another document context and moving node from a document to another is disallowed by jsdom, to "follow the browser behavior".

The issue first happens in versions 1.12.0 and 2.2.0.

#### Examples
##### Radio buttons

``` html
<input type="radio" name="rsvp" value="yes">
<input type="radio" name="rsvp" value="no">
<input type="radio" name="rsvp" value="maybe" checked>
```

Current behaviour:

``` js
$('[name=rsvp]').val();
// "yes" (first matched element’s value is returned, regardless if it’s checked or not)
```

Proposed behaviour:

``` js
$('[name=rsvp]').val();
// "maybe" (`:checked` element’s value is returned)
```
##### Checkboxes:

``` html
<input type="checkbox" name="contact" value="email">
<input type="checkbox" name="contact" value="text" checked>
<input type="checkbox" name="contact" value="call" checked>
```

Current behaviour:

``` js
$('[name=contact]').val();
// "email" (first matched element’s value is returned, regardless if it’s checked or not)
```

Proposed behaviour:

``` js
$('[name=contact]').val();
// ["text", "call"] (list of `:checked` elements’ values is returned)
```
#### Rationale

It makes sense to unify the way the value of form elements can be accessed. This would allow to get a value of a form element without knowing what type the element is.
#### Interim solution

The below function can be used instead of `.val()`. All it does is add handling for checkboxes and radio buttons, as per description above.

``` js
$.fn.value = function(val) {
    var $this = $(this);

    if (val) {
        return $this.val(val);
    }

    var radio_value = function($radios) {
        return $radios.filter(':checked').val();
    }

    var checkbox_value = function($checkboxes) {
        var vals = [];

        $checkboxes.filter(':checked').each(function() {
            vals.push($(this).val());
        });

        return vals;
    }

    var $first = $this.eq(0);

    if ($first.attr('type') == 'radio') {
        return radio_value($this);
    }

    if ($first.attr('type') == 'checkbox') {
        return checkbox_value($this);
    }

    return $this.val();
}
```

