You see, jQuery's `map` do an extra `reduce` operation(concat) in a `map` function.

This works

``` javascript
var o = {myArray : {}};
  o.myArray['one'] = '1';
  o.myArray['two'] = '2';
  jQuery.each(o.myArray, function(k,v){ console.log(k, v);});
