Following [this question on stackoverflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28407643/transitionduration-as-of-jquery-1-11-1-requires-0ms-instead-of-0-by-design-or). In short:

To remove a transitionDuration from an element that already has a transitionDuration applied to it, one would call `.css({ transitionDuration : 0 })` as of jQuery 1.11.1 it requires `css({ transitionDuration : "0ms" })` or in some rare cases completely removing the style attribute.

As the example provides on stackoverflow:

``` javascript
var duration = "250ms";

$("#dot").on("click", function(){

    $(this).css({
        transitionDuration: duration,
        transitionTimingFunction: "ease",
        transform: 'translate3d(' + Math.floor(Math.random() * 20) + 1 + 'px, ' 
                                  + Math.floor(Math.random() * 20) + 1 + 'px, 0px)'
    }).text( duration );

    // As of jQuery 1.11.1 the second click on the "dot" 
    // still has the initial "250ms" transitionDuration applied to it.
    duration = 0;

});
```

