Trying to load a page fragment from a XHTML document fails giving a "SyntaxError: An invalid or illegal string was specified" (at least on Firefox). This happ

ens with the latest versions (1.11.2 and 2.1.3). It happens because the XHTML document has the XML declaration and the DOCTYPE. I think if a regular HTML file has the DOCTYPE it will also fail. If both are removed the XHTML fragment is loaded correctly. 

By changing a few lines in the buildFragment function the problem goes away (fix works on both versions):

Change:

tmp.innerHTML = wrap[ 1 ] + elem.replace( rxhtmlTag, "<$1></$2>" ) + wrap[ 2 ];

To:

