Case:
    IE 9 or 10, jQuery 1.10.2
    Select something from iframe
    Submit iframe's form
    Select something from body or iframe 
Result: 
    SCRIPT70: Permission denied 
Reson:
      This haapens beacuase iframe document is assigned to "document" variable and if  iframe has been reloaded, IE will throw "permission denied" error when accessing "document" variable, IE do not support the defaultView property so parent will be undefined.
Fix:
       In the Sizzle function in jquery-1.10.2.js, before following condition
if ( ( context ? context.ownerDocument || context : preferredDoc ) !== document ) {
        setDocument( context );
    }

add following condition

try {
        document === document;
    }
    catch (err) {
        document = window.document; //resets document, and no more permission denied errors.
    }
Including above line of code will resolve the error.

